 <h2 id="BackupFilePath">BackupFilePath</h2>

 <p>Backup <i>FilePath</i> to a SQLite database file and access later.</p>

 <p>It could be regarded as a simple versioning system as it is similar,
 though a backup system was chosen to imply that is not to replace a
 proper versioning system. It is probably something in between as it
 is not to replace a proper dedicated backup system either.
 As it is full content backup, it could also be used to store
 different variations of a file.</p>

 <p>A versioning system is incremental differencing, while this is
 full content backup. It can be used within a directory based version
 system like Git without conflict. It can do this as it is only for the
 target file. It is suitable for temporary backups or can be long term
 use like a versioning system. The later is inefficient based on the
 size increase of the database and might be better instead with a
 proper versioning system.</p>

 <p>The database name will be like <code>filename.ext.backups</code>
 if the target file is named <code>filename.ext</code>.</p>

 <p>Modes:</p>

 <dl>
  <dt>Commit filepath</dt>
  <dd>Read <i>FilePath</i> and insert into the database.
  The full content is saved as a type blob.</dd>

  <dt>Compact the database</dt>
  <dd>Vacuum the database to reduce file size after edits or deletions.</dd>

  <dt>Delete any commit</dt>
  <dd>Select any commit to delete that commit.</dd>

  <dt>Delete the database</dt>
  <dd>Removes the database permanently from the file system.</dd>

  <dt>Edit any commit</dt>
  <dd>Select any commit to edit as a temporary file within SciTE
  and then commit back into the database.</dd>

  <dt>Edit the database</dt>
  <dd>Edit the database with an installed DB Browser for SQLite.</dd>

  <dt>Open any commit</dt>
  <dd>Select any commit to open a new tab and insert the content
  into the editor pane.</dd>

  <dt>Print all comments</dt>
  <dd>Print all comments from the database to the output pane.</dd>

  <dt>Restore any commit</dt>
  <dd>Opens a list with multiple modes:
   <div style="padding-top: 10px">
    <dl>
     <dt>Restore any commit to edit pane</dt>
     <dd>Select any commit to clear the content and then insert the
     content from the commit into the editor pane.</dd>

     <dt>Restore any commit to filepath</dt>
     <dd>Select any commit to write the content to <i>FilePath</i>.</dd>
    </dl>
   </div>
  </dd>

  <dt>WinMerge any commit</dt>
  <dd>Opens a list with multiple modes:
   <div style="padding-top: 10px">
    <dl>
     <dt>WinMerge any commit with filepath</dt>
     <dd>Compares 1 commit with <i>FilePath</i> in 2-way mode.</dd>

     <dt>WinMerge any commit with filepath 3-way</dt>
     <dd>Compares 2 commits with <i>FilePath</i> in 3-way mode.</dd>

     <dt>WinMerge any commit with blank</dt>
     <dd>Compares 1 commit with a blank pane in 2-way mode.</dd>

     <dt>WinMerge any commit with blank 3-way</dt>
     <dd>Compares 2 commits with a blank pane in 3-way mode.</dd>

     <dt>WinMerge any commit with any commit</dt>
     <dd>Compares 2 commits in 2-way mode.</dd>

     <dt>WinMerge any commit with any commit 3-way</dt>
     <dd>Compares 3 commits in 3-way mode.</dd>

     <dt>WinMerge any commit with next commit</dt>
     <dd>Compares 2 commits in 2-way mode.</dd>

     <dt>WinMerge any commit with next commit 3-way</dt>
     <dd>Compares 3 commits in 3-way mode.</dd>
    </dl>
   </div>
  </dd>
 </dl>

 <p>The 2-way merge mode will be <code>left -&gt; right</code> while the
 3-way merge mode will be <code>left -&gt; middle &lt;- right</code>.
 The <i>FilePath</i> is expected to be the 2nd pane unless
 only commits are selected for comparison or the
 <i>Edit a commit</i> compare button is used, in which
 <i>FilePath</i> will be in the left pane as read-only to
 update the commit being edited. The other panes will be for
 the temporary commit files that will be set for read-only initially.
 Next commit mode selects commits in incrementing order so that
 in 3-way mode will be <code>1st -&gt; 2nd -&gt; 3rd</code>
 and all panes will be read-only.
 WinMerge can swap panes if a different order is preferred.</p>

 <p>The next commit merge mode allows any commit to be selected
 and following commits will be automatically selected as well. Example,
 in next commit merge 3-way mode, if the 5th commit is selected,
 then the 6th and 7th commits will complete the 3-way comparison
 requirements. If the next commit is out of bounds, then the
 remaining selections will be blank. WinMerge will open blank
 panes for these blank selections so you are free to use these
 blank panes to your advantage, whatever that might be.
 The next commit merge mode saves time and saves remembering
 the last selection by avoiding the selection of each commit manually.</p>

 <p>Blank panes in WinMerge can load any file by right clicking
 on the panes title bar and select <i>Open...</i> which will open
 a dialog to choose a file to load into the blank pane.</p>

 <p><i>Edit a commit</i> shows a strip with a comment that can be changed.
 Changing tabs may cause the strip to close and reopen. The comment in
 the strip will return to the initial comment. Edit the editor pane
 content first, then change the comment just before the commit.</p>



 <h2 id="ClearAll">ClearAll</h2>

 <p>Clear all annotations and marks.</p>



 <h2 id="ClearAnnotations">ClearAnnotations</h2>

 <p>Clear all annotations.</p>



 <h2 id="ClearBookmarks">ClearBookmarks</h2>

 <p>Clear all bookmarks.</p>

 <p>Does same action as <code>Search -> Clear All Bookmarks</code>
 from the SciTE editor menu.</p>



 <h2 id="ClearErrormarks">ClearErrormarks</h2>

 <p>Clear all error marks created by double click on red error lines in the
 output pane.</p>



 <h2 id="ClearOthermarks">ClearOthermarks</h2>

 <p>Clear marks that programs may add.</p>

 <p>The user may not see these marks unless were added by a
 custom script or program.</p>



 <h2 id="CopyFileDir">CopyFileDir</h2>

 <p>Copy file directory path to the clipboard.</p>



 <h2 id="CopyFileName">CopyFileName</h2>

 <p>Copy filename without extension to the clipboard.</p>



 <h2 id="CopyFileNameExt">CopyFileNameExt</h2>

 <p>Copy filename with extension to the clipboard.</p>



 <h2 id="CopyFilePath">CopyFilePath</h2>

 <p>Copy absolute file path to the clipboard.</p>



 <h2 id="CurSelCountBraces">CurSelCountBraces</h2>

 <p>Count braces in current selection. Prints the result to the output pane.</p>

 <p>Braces:</p>

 <ul>
  <li><code>( )</code></li>
  <li><code>{ }</code></li>
  <li><code>[ ]</code></li>
  <li><code>&lt; &gt;</code></li>
 </ul>



 <h2 id="DiffFileNameExt">DiffFileNameExt</h2>

 <p>Diff <i>FileNameExt</i> with fossil or git.</p>

 <p>Prints the diff to the output pane.</p>



 <h2 id="EmptyUndoBuffer">EmptyUndoBuffer</h2>

 <p>Empty the undo buffer for the editor and output panes.</p>

 <p>Can be useful when editing a document in a long session
 and the previous undo history is not wanted. Only use if
 sure that the current undo history is not needed.</p>

 <p>Since Change History was added to SciTE,
 Change History will be disabled to synchronize with the
 emptied buffers and then set back to the previous setting.</p>

 <p>This item may not be available if the editor buffer
 is unsaved or no undo/redo stored for both buffers.</p>



 <h2 id="EskilFilePath">EskilFilePath</h2>

 <p>Run Eskil to diff <i>FilePath</i> with a checkout.</p>

 <p>Eskil expected location:&nbsp;
 <code>"$(SciteDefaultHome)\eskil\eskil.exe"</code>.</p>



 <h2 id="FrhedFilePath">FrhedFilePath</h2>

 <p>Run Frhed to hex edit <i>FilePath</i>.</p>

 <p>Frhed expected location:&nbsp;
 <code>"$(SciteDefaultHome)\frhed\frhed.exe"</code>.</p>



 <h2 id="GotoPosition">GotoPosition</h2>

 <p>Goto a position in the current document.</p>

 <p>Sometimes an error message will give a character position
 instead of a line number and column number. This dialog may help
 to goto the position quicker than manually trying to get there.</p>

 <p>Current position is default value to goto the current position
 if lost in the current view.</p>



 <h2 id="InsertCtrlCharacter">InsertCtrlCharacter</h2>

 <p>Insert a control character.</p>

 <p>Some of the most used control characters are Horizontal Tab,
 Carriage Return and Line Feed.</p>

 <p>Control characters are between the range of 0 to 32 and might
 be unusual to insert by the keyboard or by other means.</p>



 <h2 id="InsertDate">InsertDate</h2>

 <p>Insert date at position of caret.</p>

 <p>If <code>yyyy-mm-dd</code> pattern with digits is selected,
 the selection will be replaced with current date.</p>



 <h2 id="OpenAbbrevFile">OpenAbbrevFile</h2>

 <p>Open a <i>abbrev.properties</i> file which is searched
 in the subfolders of <i>SciteDefaultHome</i>.</p>



 <h2 id="OpenApiFile">OpenApiFile</h2>

 <p>Open a api file which is searched in
 <code>"$(SciteDefaultHome)\api"</code>.</p>



 <h2 id="OpenChmFile">OpenChmFile</h2>

 <p>Open a chm file which is searched in the subfolders of
 <i>SciteDefaultHome</i>.</p>

 <p>Some other locations may be searched, example <i>scite.chm</i>
 in the root of <i>SciteDefaultHome</i>.</p>



 <h2 id="OpenFileDir">OpenFileDir</h2>

 <p>Open the file directory in a file browser like explorer.</p>



 <h2 id="OpenHtaFile">OpenHtaFile</h2>

 <p>Open a hta file which is searched in the subfolders
 of <i>SciteDefaultHome</i>.</p>



 <h2 id="OpenLastClosedFile">OpenLastClosedFile</h2>

 <p>Open the last closed file.</p>

 <p>The last closed file value will be nil at the startup of SciTE.
 The item will not be listed in GlobalTools if the value is nil.</p>



 <h2 id="OpenLuaExtensionFile">OpenLuaExtensionFile</h2>

 <p>Open a lua extension file which is searched as <i>extension.lua</i>
 in the subfolders of <i>SciteDefaultHome</i>.</p>



 <h2 id="OpenSciteVarsFile">OpenSciteVarsFile</h2>

 <p>Open <i>scitevars.cfg</i> file which can be used by PrintSciteVars.</p>



 <h2 id="OpenTempFile">OpenTempFile</h2>

 <p>Open a temporary file with the same file extension
 as the current file.</p>

 <p>The file will be a temporary file created in the
 users TEMP directory that will be deleted when closed.
 Suitable for quick tests of a small amount of code
 or short lived notes. If the content is useful,
 then suggest using the menu option in SciTE
 <code>File -&gt; Save a Copy...</code> before
 closing the file that will be deleted.</p>

 <p>This is recommended only for temporary use!</p>



 <h2 id="PrintApiKeywords">PrintApiKeywords</h2>

 <p>Print keywords from api files, like those used in autocomplete.</p>



 <h2 id="PrintApiLuaPropFiles">PrintApiLuaPropFiles</h2>

 <p>Print api, lua and properties files.</p>



 <h2 id="PrintAsciiTable">PrintAsciiTable</h2>

 <p>Print an ASCII table to the output pane.</p>

 <p>Includes Extended ASCII. May need to have the codepage
 set to 0 to show the Extended ASCII correct.</p>



 <h2 id="PrintBookmarks">PrintBookmarks</h2>

 <p>Print all lines with bookmarks.</p>



 <h2 id="PrintChangeHistory">PrintChangeHistory</h2>

 <p>Print all lines with change marks.</p>

 <p>Change marks are all states like modified, reverted and saved.</p>



 <h2 id="PrintCommentLines">PrintCommentLines</h2>

 <p>Get comment lines from the editor pane and print to the output pane.</p>

 <p>Filetypes supported:</p>

 <ul>
  <li>au3</li>
  <li>cmd</li>
  <li>lua</li>
  <li>pas</li>
  <li>php</li>
  <li>properties</li>
  <li>ps1</li>
  <li>py</li>
 </ul>



 <h2 id="PrintCommentedCodeLines">PrintCommentedCodeLines</h2>

 <p>Get comment code lines from the editor pane and print to the output pane.</p>

 <p>Same filetypes supported as PrintCommentLines.</p>



 <h2 id="PrintFindText">PrintFindText</h2>

 <p>Print search results found from selected text or current word.</p>

 <p>Like the find and search built into SciTE, except this can print the
 results to the output pane.</p>

 <p>Based on code from <i>http://lua-users.org/wiki/SciteMiscScripts</i> .</p>



 <h2 id="PrintGlobalNames">PrintGlobalNames... PrintGlobalTables...</h2>

 <p>Print Lua names and tables.</p>

 <p>Used for viewing and debugging the Lua internals which is why it is
 included as a extended tool for use as it is for special use.</p>



 <h2 id="PrintPropertyList">PrintPropertyList</h2>

 <p>Print a list of property names and values modified by
 <i>SetProperty</i> or <i>SetStyle</i>.</p>

 <p>If the list is empty, then this item will not show in the ListBox.</p>

 <p>If testing property values, then the printed list can be
 copied permanently into the User Options file if desired.</p>

 <p>A list can also help to know what has changed and what can be set
 back to default. If <i>Default</i> is set for a recorded property in
 <i>SetProperty</i> or <i>SetStyle</i>, then that property will be
 removed from the list.</p>



 <h2 id="PrintReminders">PrintReminders</h2>

 <p>Find reminder lines in the edit pane and print to the output pane.</p>

 <p>Currently searches for these words with a trailing colon:</p>

 <ul>
  <li><code>debug:</code></li>
  <li><code>reminder:</code></li>
  <li><code>test:</code></li>
  <li><code>testing:</code></li>
  <li><code>todo:</code></li>
 </ul>

 <p>Based on code from RSciTE.</p>



 <h2 id="PrintSciteVars">PrintSciteVars</h2>

 <p>Print SciTE property variables.</p>

 <p>By default, prints the standard variables defined in <i>SciTEDoc.html</i>.
 If <i>scitevars.cfg</i> is located in <i>SciteDefaultHome</i>, the file will
 be read for property variable names and will include them. Comment lines
 starting with <code>;</code> or <code>#</code> will be ignored when the
 file is read.</p>



 <h2 id="ReplaceSelEscape">ReplaceSelEscape</h2>

 <p>Escapes certain special characters used in some languages.</p>

 <p>Currently does api, bat, cmd, hta, html, lua, py, pyw, sql.</p>

 <p>Escaping in general is very broad, though an example is for html:</p>

 <code><pre>&amp;</pre></code>

 <p>changes to:</p>

 <code><pre>&amp;amp;</pre></code>



 <h2 id="ReplaceSelSortLines">ReplaceSelSortLines</h2>

 <p>Sorts a selection of text by line.</p>

 <p>Example:</p>

 <code><pre>item3
item1
item2</pre></code>

 <p>changes to:</p>

 <code><pre>item1
item2
item3</pre></code>

 <p>Modes:</p>

 <dl>
  <dt>Sensitive</dt>
  <dd>Upper letters first.</dd>

  <dt>Insensitive lower compare</dt>
  <dd>All letters converted to lower before compare.</dd>

  <dt>Insensitive upper compare</dt>
  <dd>All letters converted to upper before compare.</dd>

  <dt>Sensitive reverse</dt>
  <dt>Insensitive lower compare reverse</dt>
  <dt>Insensitive upper compare reverse</dt>
  <dd>Like first 3 modes though in reverse order.</dd>
 </dl>



 <h2 id="ReplaceSelSortList">ReplaceSelSortList</h2>

 <p>Sorts a JSON style list.</p>

 <p>Example:</p>

 <code><pre>["item3", "item1", "item2"]</pre></code>

 <p>changes to:</p>

 <code><pre>["item1", "item2", "item3"]</pre></code>



 <h2 id="ReplaceSelWrapList">ReplaceSelWrapList</h2>

 <p>Wraps a JSON style list.</p>

 <p>Example:</p>

 <code><pre>["item1", "item2", "item3"]</pre></code>

 <p>changes to:</p>

 <code><pre>["item1",
 "item2",
 "item3"]</pre></code>



 <h2 id="SelectCalltipColour">SelectCalltipColour</h2>

 <p>Change colours of both autocomplete and calltip popups.</p>



 <h2 id="SetChangeHistory">SetChangeHistory</h2>

 <p>Set the view option for Change History.</p>

 <p>Options are:</p>

 <dl>
  <dt>None</dt>
  <dd>Tracking only.</dd>

  <dt>Markers</dt>
  <dd>Tracking with margin markers.</dd>

  <dt>Indicators</dt>
  <dd>Tracking with inline indicators.</dd>

  <dt>Markers and Indicators</dt>
  <dd>Tracking with margin markers and inline indicators.</dd>
 </dl>

 <p>Options are applied in an instant and will affect the Change History view for all documents.</p>

 <p>Disable tracking is not provided here as that option makes this tool unusable.</p>



 <h2 id="SetColour">SetColour</h2>

 <p>Set a value for a colour variable name with fore and back
 colours using a Colour Dialog.</p>

 <p><i>Default</i> item will only unmask and remove property names
 starting with <code>"colour."</code> from the recorded list.</p>

 <p>Changes should not affect the ToggleDimComments feature so
 SetColour should be considered before SetProperty or SetStyle
 for changing colours.</p>

 <p>Some of the colours names are not standard for the official SciTE
 distribution so may only function properly with this custom setup.</p>



 <h2 id="SetProperty">SetProperty</h2>

 <p>Set a property and it's value for the duration of the
 current SciTE instance.</p>

 <p>This can be useful for temporary needs. Example of changing
 <i>export.html.wysiwyg</i> to another value so the
 <code>File -&gt; Export -&gt; To HTML</code> menu item saves the
 output in another HTML format. Another example is to change some
 of the wrapping property values to display wrapping differently.
 Or another example, the user just wants to test a property
 with different values for discovery.</p>

 <p>Some predefined list items:</p>

 <dl>
  <dt>Default</dt>
  <dd>The property will be unmasked to use it's
  real value as set in the properties file.</dd>

  <dt>Empty</dt>
  <dd>The property will be set with an empty value.</dd>

  <dt>SelectColour</dt>
  <dd>Colour Dialog will show to allow selection of a colour.</dd>

  <dt>SelectProperty</dt>
  <dd>InputBox will show to enter property name and
  a second InputBox will show to enter the value.</dd>
 </dl>

 <p>All other items will be displayed as <code>number = description</code>
 for good user interpretation with the appended descriptions.
 Only the initial number is used as the value to set the property.
 If the item starts without a number, the item will be treated as
 a value that needs special handling.</p>

 <p>One property with special handling is <i>font.monospace</i>.
 The items are the actual property values. Items are added to the
 list depending on the value of the <i>technology</i> property. Some
 3rd party fonts will be added to the list if selected <i>Yes</i>
 with the messagebox. These 3rd party fonts can be downloaded from:</p>

 <dl>
  <dt>Cascadia Code, Cascadia Mono</dt>
  <dd><i>https://github.com/microsoft/cascadia-code</i></dd>

  <dt>Fira Code</dt>
  <dd><i>https://github.com/tonsky/FiraCode</i></dd>

  <dt>JetBrains Mono</dt>
  <dd><i>https://github.com/JetBrains/JetBrainsMono</i></dd>

  <dt>Source Code Pro</dt>
  <dd><i>https://github.com/adobe-fonts/source-code-pro</i></dd>
 </dl>

 <p>Fonts will not display ligatures when technology is GDI, so
  the list may be different based on technology in use.</p>

 <p><i>Cascadia Mono</i> is <i>Cascadia</i> without the ligatures,
 which will only be listed when technology is <i>DirectWrite</i>.
 <i>Courier</i> will only be listed if technology is GDI.</p>



 <h2 id="SetStyle">SetStyle</h2>

 <p>Set a style and it's value for the duration of the
 current SciTE instance.</p>

 <p>Just like SetProperty as a style is a property,
 except this will focus only on the current language style.</p>

 <p>The preset item for selection will be based at the caret position.
 For example, if the caret is at a keyword in Lua, then
 <i>style.lua.5</i> will be highlighted for selection.</p>

 <p><i>Default</i> item will only unmask and remove property names
 of the current language from the recorded list.</p>

 <p><code>"GlobalSettings['style_by_colour']"</code> in
 <i>SciTEStartup.lua</i> has 3 possible values:</p>

 <dl>
  <dt>true</dt>
  <dd>Always use a Colour Dialog to set a foreground colour.</dd>

  <dt>false</dt>
  <dd>Always use an InputBox to edit the expanded value as text.</dd>

  <dt>nil</dt>
  <dd>Show a MsgBox to select true or false for the duration
  of the SciTE instance. This is the default unless modified.
 </dl>

 <p>The Colour Dialog is probably suitable for quick changes,
 though it currently does only the foreground colour. Options
 such as unmasking a value or to set an empty value currently
 is not implemented.</p>

 <p>The InputBox allows editing the expanded value of the style.
 This means that for example <i>style.lua.5</i> will not be the actual
 value of <code>"$(colour.keyword),bold"</code>, instead will be like
 the expanded format of <code>"fore:#88BBEF,bold"</code>. Changing
 the value will save the expanded value so the variable name is
 lost unless the unexpanded format is entered or the style is
 unmasked to use the actual value once again.</p>

 <p>The ToggleDimComments feature may not work with
 comment styles that have lost any variable names.</p>

 <p>Some style names may not appear in the list if their values are empty.
 Detection of style names is based on not being empty and will search for
 index numbers from 0 to 127.</p>



 <h2 id="StartExeFile">StartExeFile</h2>

 <p>Run executables in the subfolders of <i>SciteDefaultHome</i>.</p>

 <p>Executables can be added to subfolders, such as Frhed.
 StartExeFile will run these executables without any arguments.</p>



 <h2 id="StripTrailingSpaces">StripTrailingSpaces</h2>

 <p>Strip trailing spaces from the current document in the edit pane.</p>

 <p>SciTE can be set to strip whitespace characters at end of lines.
 This tool allows the user to strip the end of lines in the edit pane.
 Can be useful if the property of <i>strip.trailing.spaces</i> is not
 used globally or by the current filepattern.</p>



 <h2 id="ToggleCodePage">ToggleCodePage</h2>

 <p>Toggle between 0 (ANSI), 65001 (UTF8) and the actual codepage.</p>



 <h2 id="ToggleDimComments">ToggleDimComments</h2>

 <p>Toggle comment colours from normal colour to a lighter colour.</p>

 <p>Dimming may not be useful for general programming though debugging
 code with dimmed comments may help with focus. Toggles on or off.</p>



 <h2 id="ToggleExtendedTools">ToggleExtendedTools</h2>

 <p>Toggle the ListBox to show or hide the extended tools.</p>

 <p>Initially, some tools may not be shown in the ListBox, due to not being
 suitable for regular use. This option allows the user to toggle the list by
 reshowing the ListBox with or without the extended tools. Toggles on or off.</p>



 <h2 id="ToggleHighlightCurrentWord">ToggleHighlightCurrentWord</h2>

 <p>Toggle highlight current word at position of the caret.</p>

 <p>For distraction free programming, default to off.
 Toggles on or off.</p>



 <h2 id="ToggleMonospaceFont">ToggleMonospaceFont</h2>

 <p>Toggle with monospace font and proportional font.</p>

 <p>If <i>font.override</i> property has been appended to
 global font properties, default font is monospace.
 This function allows proportional font.</p>



 <h2 id="WinMergeFilePath">WinMergeFilePath</h2>

 <p>If <i>left</i> and possibly <i>middle</i> are set, then <i>FilePath</i>
 will be the last argument to WinMerge.</p>

 <p>If not <i>left</i> is set then will pass <i>FilePath</i> as 1st argument to WinMerge.
 WinMerge will then show the <i>Select Files or Folders dialog</i>.
 Choose your settings and then press the <i>Compare</i> button.</p>

 <p>WinMerge expected location:&nbsp;
 <code>"%ProgramFiles%\WinMerge\WinMergeU.exe"</code>.</p>



 <h2 id="WinMergeFilePathLeft">WinMergeFilePath left</h2>

 <p>Stores the <i>FilePath</i> as 1st argument for the latter use of WinMergeFilePath.</p>

 <p>Works similar to the WinMerge advanced context menu entries.</p>



 <h2 id="WinMergeFilePathMiddle">WinMergeFilePath middle</h2>

 <p>Stores the <i>FilePath</i> as 2nd argument for the latter use of WinMergeFilePath.</p>

 <p>Works similar to the WinMerge advanced context menu entries.</p>



 <h2 id="WinMergeFilePathUnsaved">WinMergeFilePath unsaved</h2>

 <p>Compares the edit pane content with <i>FilePath</i>
 or another files content.</p>

 <p>The edit pane of SciTE is read and saved to a temporary file
 and is passed as the 1st file argument to WinMerge.
 The <i>FilePath</i> is passed as the 2nd file argument to WinMerge.
 If <i>FilePath</i> does not exist, like with a Untitled document,
 then only the 1st file argument is passed so that WinMerge will
 display the option to select the 2nd item to compare.</p>

 <p>This can be useful if you do not know the difference between the
 edit pane content and the file content. Especially if a messagebox asks
 to reload from file to determine whether to save or not after the reload.
 If the later is the case, select <i>No</i> to the messagebox and then use
 this tool to compare. <code>File -> Revert</code> menu item can be used if
 <i>FilePath</i> on disk is wanted after the compare is done.</p>

 <p>If <i>FilePath</i> does not exist, then comparing a temporary file
 to another file might be useful. Example, open a commit from
 <i>BackupFilePath</i> into a new tab and then select this item
 to compare the edit pane content with a file selected in WinMerge.</p>

